    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush's Priorities</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Paul Smith letter on June 19 article holds example of George W Bush's 'practical intelligence' also reveals much about his priorities</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In an anecdote meant to illustrate George W. Bush's ''practical intelligence'' (front page, June 19), we're told that he was able to name all 55 fellow fraternity pledges during a hazing. So why wasn't he able to name a handful of world leaders during the famed ''ambush interview''?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In an anecdote meant to illustrate George W. Bush's ''practical intelligence'' (front page, June 19), we're told that he was able to name all 55 fellow fraternity pledges during a hazing. So why wasn't he able to name a handful of world leaders during the famed ''ambush interview''?</p>
        <p>Doesn't this tell us more about Mr. Bush's priorities than it does his abilities?</p>
        <p>PAUL SMITH  Bay View, Wis., June 19, 2000</p>
      </block>
